:"https://github.com/remix-run/react-router/issues/8073#issuecomment-931778385","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/remix-run/react-router/issues/8073","id":931778385,"node_id":"IC_kwDOAS86yM43ic9R","user":{"login":"eshy","id":322731,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjMyMjczMQ==","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/322731?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/eshy","html_url":"https://github.com/eshy","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/eshy/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/eshy/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/eshy/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/eshy/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/eshy/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/eshy/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/eshy/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/eshy/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/eshy/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2021-09-30T23:32:14Z","updated_at":"2021-09-30T23:32:14Z","body":"This change is a bad design. \r\n\r\nBeing able to easily access parent route params make it simple to split route definitions.\r\nRemoving that option requires passing parameters down to children, multiple levels in some cases. \r\n\r\nThe stated goal in the release notes states this is to make components with Routes portable but if you need that, just don't use parent params.\r\nLet me make that choice when I'm building my app instead of forcing me to pass parameters down. \r\n\r\nI have a feeling this solution is for a less used scenario as well.\r\n","author_association":"NONE","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/remix-run/react-router/issues/comments/931778385/reactions","total_count":1,"+1":1,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null,"