ents{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/svenheden/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2021-10-01T11:45:03Z","updated_at":"2021-10-01T11:45:03Z","body":"> This change is a bad design.\r\n> \r\n> Being able to easily access parent route params make it simple to split route definitions. Removing that option requires passing parameters down to children, multiple levels in some cases.\r\n> \r\n> The stated goal in the release notes states this is to make components with Routes portable but if you need that, just don't use parent params. Let me make that choice when I'm building my app instead of forcing me to pass parameters down.\r\n> \r\n> I have a feeling this solution is for a less used scenario as well.\r\n\r\nI strongly agree with this, and was surprised when I read @mjackson's reply that this is intentional. From my experience it's a very common use case to want to read parent route params, and to no longer have support for this in the router itself feels less than ideal.","author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/remix-run/react-router/issues/comments/932157130/reactions","total_count":2,"+1":2,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null,"event":"commented","actor":{"login":"svenheden","id":76098,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjc2MDk4","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/76098?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/svenheden","html_url":"https://github.com/svenheden","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/svenheden/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/svenheden/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/svenheden/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/svenheden/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/svenheden/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https: